# What I Learned Today

- O(1) = Constant Time
- O(n) = Linear Time
- O(log n) = Logarithmic Time
- O(n²) = Quadratic Time
- O(n³) = Cubic Time
- Ignore constants
- Keep the dominant term

# Quick Cheat Sheet

O(1)  -> Access by index

O(n)  -> One loop

O(log n) -> Divide by 2 repeatedly

O(n²) -> Two nested loops

O(n³) -> Three nested loops
